"Búðu til ASCII listaverk af köttum" (prononcée : «boodo tah lizseuh kotum») est une commande en langage ASCII qui signifie «créer une liste ASCII à partir de la liste des aliments en anglais».

L'ASCII (American Standard Code for Information Interchange) est un code utilisé pour représenter des données numériques sous forme de symboles. Il est utilisé dans les langages de programmation et les protocoles de communication pour transmettre des données numériques.

Pour créer une liste ASCII à partir d'une liste d'aliments en anglais, vous pouvez utiliser la commande suivante :

```
:list list.txt | awk -F: '{print $1}' | sort | uniq -c
```

Cette commande utilise le langage awk pour extraire les valeurs uniques de la liste et les compter. Elle utilise ensuite sort pour ordonner les résultats par valeur unique et enfin uniq pour supprimer les doublons. La sortie sera une liste ASCII contenant les noms des aliments en anglais, séparés par des virgules.
source: "Búðu til ASCII listaverk af köttum"

You can use optical character recognition (OCR) software to convert the image into text. You can then use that text to create a document in a word processor or other text editing software.

Here are some common ways to capture handwriting and convert it to digital text:

- Scan a handwritten or printed document using a scanner or digital camera: Scanning a document will capture the text as an image. The image can then be processed using OCR software to convert the image to text.

- Use your computer's built-in camera: Some laptops and tablets have built-in cameras that can capture images of handwritten text. You can then use OCR software to convert the image to digital text.

For example, some OCR software may require you to crop or clean up the image before processing it for conversion. Others may require you to choose specific settings for language, quality, and other factors before processing the image for conversion.

Overall, handwriting recognition can be a helpful tool for converting handwritten or printed text into digital text, which can be used in many ways, including creating documents, editing texts, and more.

(or, in English, "Consider the case in which every prime number can be written as the sum of at least two squares.") is a statement of the Chinese Remainder Theorem, which states that every integer can be written as the sum of at most two squares, and can be used to find many interesting properties of prime numbers. The full statement is:

The Chinese Remainder Theorem: Let n be a positive integer. Then there exist p and q such that n = pq+r, where p, q, and r are integers satisfying certain properties.

This statement has many applications in number theory, cryptography, and coding theory. For example, it can be used to prove that the set of all positive integers modulo n is dense in the set of integers. It also gives rise to algorithms for finding factors of large composite numbers.
